40:"The Automatic Lock is included in 8500W.";i:51;s:43:"Cellular data or Wi-Fi connection required.";i:52;s:91:"After experiencing a power outage it may be necessary to reconnect your garage door opener.";i:53;s:208:"Because the garage door requires electricity in order to open and close with ease this is something that can be shut down due to an electric failure in the event of a storm or other common power outage cause.";i:54;s:52:"This morning I found myself locked out of my garage.";i:55;s:63:"My interior wall opener isnt working and neither is the remote.";i:56;s:64:"The light on the interior pad is out suggesting a loss of power.";i:57;s:138:"Unfortunately my fuse box is inside the garage and I I have no way of entering unless I can disable the opener and manually open the door.";i:58;s:60:"How to Open Your Garage Door Manually When The Power Is Out.";i:59;s:79:"Ensure your garage door is fully closed then disconnect the garage door opener.";i:60;s:75:"Pull the emergency cord to disconnect the door from the garage door opener.";i:61;s:103:"The cord usually has a red handle and will hang down from the center rail of the garage door mechanism.";i:62;s:62:"Lift the garage door straight up until the door is fully open.";i:63;s:129:"Even if your garage door motor wont operate a garage door if it has been successfully re-engaged then the door is usually locked.";i:64;s:62:"Test trying to open the door manually to confirm it is locked.";i:65;s:76:"If you cannot lift the door manually then the door is locked with the motor.";i:66;s:129:"If your motor will not re-engage and the door can still be opened manually for security you might wish to manually lock the door.";i:67;s:63:"This is a garage door that auto locks itself when it is closed.";i:68;s:123:"It is a spring lock type door that when pulled down it springs the things on each side of the door and you cant pull it up.";i:69;s:39:"I think its called a tension cord lock.";i:70;s:65:"Well now I am outside the garag